Docs.remarks: Poisson regression is a parameterized regression method. It assumes that the log of the conditional mean of the dependent variable follows a linear function of the dependent variables. Assuming that the dependent variable follows a Poisson distribution, the parameters of the regressor can be estimated by maximizing the likelihood of the obtained observations.
